  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd3 \u0dc0\u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dbb \u0dba\u0ddc\u0daf\u0db1 \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd4\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dba \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0db8\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0da0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dba \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dca\u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A professor's recommendation about the rate of fertilizer application to paddy cultivation",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Agriculture professors have recommended that 70 percent of chemical fertilizers and 30 percent of organic fertilizers be applied to paddy cultivation in the 2022/23 season.",
        "The opinions and suggestions of agricultural sector scholars regarding how to use chemical and organic fertilizers for paddy cultivation were conducted today (28) at the Ministry of Agriculture.",
        "A group of officers including Professor Buddhi Marambe, Professor Varshi Dandeniya, Professor Saman Dharmakirthi, Dr. Upul Ratnayake, Secretary of the Ministry, Rohana Pushpakumara, Director General of the Department of Agriculture, Dr. Ajantha De Silva participated in this discussion which was chaired by the Minister of Agriculture, Mr. Mahinda Maraweera, through Zoom technology. ."
      ],
